subject: Re: [junit] Implicit super constructor TestCase() is not visible for default constructor. Mu
msgSnippet: Hi, I looked it up in the Eclipse Help- About Eclipse- Plug-in-Details. it is defenately 3.8.1. I also removed all other junit.jars I had in the project path
messageBody:
Hi,
I looked it up in the Eclipse Help->About Eclipse->Plug-in-Details. it
is defenately 3.8.1.
I also removed all other junit.jars I had in the project path and still
had the problem. But in meantime
it works. I don't know why, because I changed everything back to initial
state and I don't get the error
message any more.
I hope it stays like this.

Thanks for your help!
Andreas
